# Building Modern Web Apps with TypeScript

TypeScript has become an essential tool in modern web development. Here's why I use it for all my projects.

## Type Safety

One of the biggest advantages is catching errors at compile time rather than runtime. This means:

- Fewer bugs in production
- Better developer experience with autocomplete
- Easier refactoring

## Better Tooling

With TypeScript, your IDE can provide:

1. Intelligent code completion
2. Inline documentation
3. Refactoring tools

## The Learning Curve

While TypeScript adds complexity initially, the long-term benefits far outweigh the initial learning investment.

```typescript
interface User {
  name: string;
  email: string;
  role: 'admin' | 'user';
}

function greetUser(user: User): string {
  return `Hello, ${user.name}!`;
}
```

The type system helps catch bugs before they happen.
